warm palette.

## Typography

| Role           | Family              | Weight | Size              |
|----------------|---------------------|--------|-------------------|
| Display / Hero | Cormorant Garamond  | 300    | clamp(56px,8vw,96px) |
| Section titles | Cormorant Garamond  | 300    | clamp(36px,5vw,56px) |
| Card titles    | Cormorant Garamond  | 400    | 28–32px           |
| Body           | Karla               | 400    | 15–16px           |
| Body small     | Karla               | 400    | 13–14px           |
| Labels/meta    | DM Mono             | 300    | 10–11px           |

Google Fonts import:
`Cormorant+Garamond:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;1,300;1,400`
`Karla:wght@300;400;500;600`
`DM+Mono:wght@300;400`

Rules:
- Cormorant Garamond for display only. Never use it for body paragraphs.
- DM Mono is for timestamps, status badges, and eyebrow labels only.
  Do not use it for navigation, body copy, or any reading context.
- Line-height: 1.7 for body, 1.1 for display headings.
- Letter-spacing: 0.2em on DM Mono labels, none on Karla body.

## Layout Principles

- Max content width: 900px for hero, 780px for modals, 680px for writing.
- Section padding: 100px 48px desktop, 64px 20px mobile.
- Grid: single column stack. No multi-column body layouts.
- Spacing scale: 8px base. Common values: 16, 24, 32, 48, 64, 100.
- Nav: fixed top, transparent until scroll > 40px, then bg rgba(246,242,235,0.94) 
  with backdrop-filter blur(20px).

## Components

### Buttons
Primary: background --terra, color #F6F2EB, padding 14px 32px, no border-radius 
(border-radius: 2px only), font-size 12px, Karla, letter-spacing 0.12em, uppercase.
Hover: background --terra-light.

Ghost: transparent background, border 1px solid --border, color --text-mid.
Hover: border-color --text-mid, color --text.

Never use rounded buttons (border-radius > 4px).

### Cards (Project cards)
Background --bg2, padding 48px 56px, 2px left border in --terra that 
scales from scaleY(0) to scaleY(1) on hover. No box-shadow. Hover 
background shifts to --bg3.

### Modals
Background --bg, border 1px solid --border, box-shadow 0 24px 64px 
rgba(26,23,20,0.14), max-width 780px (case study) or 680px (writing).
Overlay: rgba(246,242,235,0.82) with backdrop-filter blur(14px).

### Status badges
Shipped: background rgba(74,124,89,0.15), border rgba(74,124,89,0.4), 
color #3A6B48.
In Build: background --terra-dim, border rgba(196,80,26,0.3), color --terra.
Font: DM Mono, 9px, letter-spacing 0.15em, uppercase.

## Depth & Elevation
No decorative shadows on cards. Shadows reserved for modals only.
No noise overlays, no background grid patterns, no radial glows except 
one subtle radial on the hero (rgba(196,80,26,0.05)).

## Do's
- Use --terra for one thing per component. Not multiple.
- Let typography hierarchy do the work before adding colour.
- Keep section labels in DM Mono, 10px, --terra, uppercase.
- Maintain generous whitespace. When in doubt, add more.
- Use Cormorant Garamond italics (`<em>`) for one key word in hero headlines.

## Don'ts
- No custom cursor (cursor: none).
- No noise textures or grain overlays.
- No background grid lines.
- No dark mode surfaces (#0C0B09 etc.) anywhere.
- No rounded pills on primary buttons.
- No DM Mono for navigation or body text.
- No more than two font families visible at once in any section.

## Responsive
- Mobile breakpoint: 768px.
- Nav collapses to hamburger at 768px.
- Project cards go single column at 768px.
- Modal panels slide up from bottom on mobile (border-radius 12px 12px 0 0).
- Section padding reduces to 64px 20px on mobile.

## Agent Prompt Guide
Quick reference for prompting any AI with this design system:

Colors: bg #F6F2EB, text #1A1714, accent #C4501A, border #C8C4BA
Fonts: Cormorant Garamond (display), Karla (body), DM Mono (labels only)
Feel: warm editorial, text-first, no decoration, one accent

Example prompt:
"Add a testimonials section. Follow DESIGN.md: use --bg2 as background, 
Cormorant Garamond italic for the quote, Karla for attribution, DM Mono 
for the label. One --terra accent rule max."
